Description

When JIRA cannot load a service, it wraps them in an "UnloadableJiraServiceContainer" so that the user may delete them and JIRA continues to work. This wrapper does not seem to work well with the initial JIRA startup log. Where JIRA lists the services we get service listings of the form

{quote}
Exception getting Service information : java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException: This method is not supported in an UnloadableJiraServiceContainer
{quote}

We probably should not be displaying the UOE, but rather a nice description.

